    "content_hash": "ed70b21f978c59a0",
    "department": "Growth",
    "description": "About Juicebox\n\nJuicebox is on a mission to help teams win the talent war.\n\nIn the age of AI, human ingenuity is the ultimate scarce resource. Recruiting is a zero-sum game where you either compete or lose.\n\nTeams at Ramp, Notion, and leading AI labs use Juicebox to power their hiring, alongside 5,000+ customers from early-stage startups to Fortune 500 companies.\n\nWe are on the path to $100M in ARR with 20%+ monthly growth, powering thousands of searches every day and making Juicebox one of the fastest-growing AI SaaS companies in the world.\n\nJuicebox has raised over $116M in funding from lead investors including Sequoia Capital, DST Global, and NFDG. Read more about our $80M Series B https://juicebox.ai/blog/series-b here. Additional investors in Juicebox include Y Combinator, Coatue, Bond, Lux, Verified Capital, and Committed Capital.\n\nThe Role\n\nWe’re hiring a Growth Lead to own and scale Juicebox’s organic and product-led growth engine.\n\nA significant portion of Juicebox revenue already comes from our self-serve product motion. This role will focus on growing that channel through product experiments, lifecycle marketing, and user-driven growth loops.\n\nYou’ll work closely with the founders and marketing team to design experiments, launch initiatives, and drive measurable growth.\n\nYour ultimate goal will be to increase revenue from self-serve customers, and you will own that metric.\n\nYou Will\n\n - Own Juicebox’s self-serve revenue growth\n\n - Drive organic and product-led growth initiatives\n\n - Increase user invitations and product-driven adoption\n\n - Improve onboarding, activation, and referral flows\n\n - Run experiments to improve self-serve acquisition, retention, and reactivation\n\n - Launch lifecycle campaigns across email, product messaging, and promotions\n\n - Analyze product usage and growth metrics to identify opportunities\n\n - Work cross-functionally with marketing, product, and engineering to ship growth experiments\n\nYou Have\n\n - 2+ years working on growth at a B2B or B2C SaaS company (4+ preferred)\n\n - Experience with product-led growth or growth experimentation\n\n - Comfort working with product and user data\n\n - Ability to read or write SQL queries (or interpret them)\n\n - Strong ownership mentality and ability to run experiments end-to-end\n\n - High EQ and ability to collaborate across teams to ship initiatives",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
    "is_active": true,
